Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Menswear Revolution
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0b01jsy
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 30 Apr 2018
The menswear revolution: Laurie Taylor explores the transformation in men's clothing with Jay McCauley Bowstead, lecturer in Cultural and Historical Studies at London College of Fashion. Also taking part is John Harvey, Life Fellow at the University of Cambridge, and author of a book charting the history of men's dress from the toga to the suit. They're joined by Julia Twigg, Professor of Social Policy and Sociology at the University of Kent, who talks about her research on older men and fashion. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less